\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
We take the global priority vector from the first stage and multiply it
 with all the priority vectors above to get the weighted priority vectors
 for the alternatives with respect to each criterion or sub-criterion.
 Let us denote 
\begin_inset Formula $W_{x}^{y}$
\end_inset

 as the weight or the value of the weighted priority for an alternative
 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset

 which has been pairwise compared using a criterion or sub-criterion 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

.
 The table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand vref
reference "tab:Weighted-priority-vectors"

\end_inset

 shows us the exact calculations for the weighted priorities.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
